3.2/ Additionally, DeFi composability is really about coordinating and integrating with other protocols that are building on top of liquid staking protocols, increasing use cases and utility for the LS token derivatives.

3.1/ On the ecosystem level, liquid staking adds another layer of composability in DeFi, where the issued LS token derivatives can be used in other supported protocols to generate more yields.

This helps in constructing monetary and financial blocks across the ecosystem.
3/ However, liquid staking is much more than just solving liquidity problems 🤔
2.2/ At Helio Protocol, it also takes about 7-14 days to unstake BNB as well.

2.1/ Additionally, when users unstake their tokens, they have the option to withdraw their yield-bearing tokens which appreciates against the underlying token according to staking rewards instantly, instead of waiting for the unstaking period (7-14days)

2/ Why is liquid staking so important?

The obvious benefit of liquid staking comes from liquidity for users, where they have access to their staked or locked up funds/capital.

1.2/ Liquid staking solves the issue by issuing a receipt of the tokens that you have staked in the form of LS (liquid staked) tokens, which can be used for further DeFi activities (e.g; Yield farming, trading or a form of collateral for borrowing.) 👨‍🌾
1.1/ In traditional staking, delegators lose access to their funds, resulting in locked up capital not being utilised to their fullest potential.

1/ Liquid staking aims to solve the capital inefficiencies when it comes to staking tokens.

In other words, liquid staking is an improved version of the traditional staking mechanism.
